Positional shows you 5 different aspects of your location.

- **Coordinates**: Your current latitude and longitude. You can adjust their format in Settings.
- **Accuracy**: The accuracy of the coordinates.
- **Bearing**: The direction you are moving, regardless of orientation of your Android device.
- **Elevation**: Your current elevation above sea level.
- **Speed**: Your current speed.

If your device is running Android 8.0 or higher, Positional will also show you accuracies for each of these aspects. You can hide these accuracies in Settings.